        {
            "text": "For the + c \u2192 p K \u2212 \u03c0 + decay, the branching fraction determination in Ref. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "[6] is model dependent resulting in the value B( + c \u2192 p K \u2212 \u03c0 + ) = (5.0 \u00b1 1.3) % with the large uncertainty originating from the model dependence. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In this article, the branching fraction obtained as the weighted mean of the BELLE [7] and CLEO [8] measurements is used for the + c \u2192 p K \u2212 \u03c0 + decay. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
